    <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 text-center">
        <img class="img-circle img-responsive img-center" src="~/Content/Images/Logo_ruby.png" alt="">
        <h3>
            Ruby
            
        </h3>
        <p>Ruby is a human friendly language so if you speak human, you're already half way to knowing Ruby.</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary custom-button">@Html.ActionLink("Learn more", "Ruby", "Languages") </button>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 text-center">
        <img class="img-circle img-responsive img-center" src="~/Content/Images/Logo_csharp.png" alt="">
        <h3>
            C#
            
        </h3>
        <p>When you first start learning C# you'll be more on the blunt side than the sharp side, but that's okay.</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary custom-button">@Html.ActionLink("Learn more", "CSharp", "Languages") </button>
